This article is a statement by the President on the one-year anniversary of the repeal of "Don't Ask, Don't Tell." The President emphasizes that the repeal upholds American values of fairness and equality, allowing gay and lesbian Americans to serve openly in the military. He praises the professionalism of the military in implementing the change, which has strengthened national security by allowing the skills and talents of gay and lesbian service members to contribute. The President also highlights that the ability for service members to be open about their families and loved ones strengthens the integrity of the individuals and institutions within the military.